The paper deals with multi-camera video surveillance and proposes a novel representation for multi-camera video data, which can be used for clustering non-linear data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new geometry metric and extends the Low Rank Representation (LRR) model, which involves mathematical concepts and techniques, indicating that the paper may also belong to the mathematical physics (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
